      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 13
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a driver-focused example featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated M96 horizontally opposed six-cylinder engine. This power unit utilizes VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing across the rev range, mated to a precise 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox. The chassis maintains its structural integrity, utilizing MacPherson struts and a multi-link rear suspension geometry that ensures neutral handling characteristics. Significant preventative maintenance has been addressed, including an IMS bearing retrofit with a ceramic solution and a fresh rear main seal (RMS). The braking system features four-piston monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, providing excellent pedal feel and thermal management. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain remains mechanically synchronized with linear power delivery and a crisp shifter throw.",
